      "SummaryText": "een in place for years.  All employees, contractors and anyone else that is at the facility for any length of time or will work around the chlorine system is fully informed of the hazards of chlorine, the operation of the alarm system (i.e. what certain alarms mean), and how to safely exit the facility.  As a result, there has never been a reportable chlorine release at the facility.\r\n\r\nUPGRADES TO IMPROVE SAFETY\r\nAs a direct result of the Risk Management Program, the City upgraded the chlorine facilities to include an automatic shutoff system to segregate cylinders if a release occurs and a scrubber to protect plant staff and the general public."
